# Scratch Programming Curriculum for Kids (Extended Edition)
## 24 Sessions × 45 Minutes | Aligned with Singapore MOE Standards

---

## Curriculum Design Analysis

### Learning Weight Distribution

This curriculum maintains proportional learning weights from the original Code for Fun 10-hour structure while expanding to 24 sessions for deeper mastery.

| Topic | Original (600 min) | Original Weight | New (1080 min) | New Sessions | New Weight |
|-------|-------------------|-----------------|----------------|--------------|------------|
| Introduction & Sequences | 60 min | 10% | 90 min | 2 sessions | 8.3% |
| Events | 60 min | 10% | 90 min | 2 sessions | 8.3% |
| Loops | 60 min | 10% | 135 min | 3 sessions | 12.5% |
| Conditionals | 60 min | 10% | 135 min | 3 sessions | 12.5% |
| Variables | 60 min | 10% | 90 min | 2 sessions | 8.3% |
| Parallelism | 60 min | 10% | 135 min | 3 sessions | 12.5% |
| Operators | 60 min | 10% | 90 min | 2 sessions | 8.3% |
| Remix & Collaboration | 60 min | 10% | 90 min | 2 sessions | 8.3% |
| Final Project | 120 min | 20% | 225 min | 5 sessions | 20.8% |
| **Total** | **600 min** | **100%** | **1080 min** | **24 sessions** | **100%** |

**Rationale for Weight Adjustments:**
- Complex topics (Loops, Conditionals, Parallelism) receive +2.5% weight for mastery-based learning
- Foundational topics maintain similar weights
- Final project maintains ~20% weight aligned with Singapore's emphasis on application

