## Assessment Framework

### Formative Assessment (Ongoing)

Based on [Harvard's CT Assessment Instruments](https://scratched.gse.harvard.edu/ct/assessing.html):

| Method | Frequency | Focus | Recording |
|--------|-----------|-------|-----------|
| Observation | Every session | Engagement, problem-solving | Checklist |
| Exit Tickets | Sessions 1-4 | Concept understanding | Collected |
| Code Review | Sessions 7, 10, 12, 15, 17 | Correct concept use | Rubric |
| Debug Challenges | Sessions 7, 9 | Testing & debugging skills | Success rate |
| Peer Feedback | Sessions 4, 15, 18, 22 | Communication, collaboration | Forms |
| Progress Logs | Sessions 21-23 | Self-monitoring | Journal |

### Summative Assessment

#### Module Checkpoints

| Checkpoint | Session | Focus | Method |
|------------|---------|-------|--------|
| Module 1 | After Session 4 | Sequence, Events | Project review |
| Module 2 | After Session 10 | Loops, Conditionals | Maze game assessment |
| Module 3 | After Session 15 | Variables, Parallelism | Two-player game assessment |
| Module 4 | After Session 19 | Operators, Digital Citizenship | Quiz game + reflection |
| Final | Session 24 | All concepts | Capstone project |

#### Dr. Scratch Analysis Rubric

Based on [Dr. Scratch](https://www.drscratch.org/) scoring:

| Category | Basic (1) | Developing (2) | Proficient (3) |
|----------|-----------|----------------|----------------|
| **Abstraction** | More than one script, no custom blocks | Use of custom blocks | Custom blocks with parameters |
| **Parallelism** | Two scripts on green flag | Two scripts on event | Multiple scripts on multiple events |
| **Logic** | If | If-else | Logic operations (and/or/not) |
| **Synchronization** | Wait | Broadcast | Broadcast and wait |
| **Flow Control** | Sequence of blocks | Repeat, forever | Repeat until |
| **User Interactivity** | Green flag | Key/sprite pressed | Input (ask, video, sound) |
| **Data Representation** | Modifiers | Variables | Lists |

**Score Interpretation:**
- 0-7: Basic
- 8-14: Developing
- 15-21: Mastery

#### Final Project Rubric

| Criteria | Exemplary (4) | Proficient (3) | Developing (2) | Beginning (1) |
|----------|---------------|----------------|----------------|---------------|
| **CT Concepts** | Uses 6+ concepts correctly and purposefully | Uses 4-5 concepts correctly | Uses 2-3 concepts with some errors | Uses 1-2 concepts with significant errors |
| **Functionality** | Project works flawlessly with polished features | Project works with minor bugs | Project partially works | Project has major issues |
| **Creativity & Originality** | Highly original with unique features and personal voice | Shows creativity in design or features | Some personalisation | Minimal personalisation |
| **Code Quality** | Efficient code, good organization, no redundancy | Mostly efficient, minor redundancy | Some inefficiency, disorganized | Inefficient, highly disorganized |
| **Iteration & Debugging** | Clear evidence of multiple iterations, refined debugging | Shows testing and debugging | Limited evidence of debugging | No evidence of testing |
| **Presentation** | Clear, confident explanation of code logic, concepts, and challenges | Good explanation of main features | Basic description of project | Minimal explanation |

